data.chText: 被…吸引住；专心致志；全神贯注
data.enText: very interested in sth/sb so that you are not paying attention to anything else

data.chText: 她好像完全被这本书迷住了。
data.enText: She seemed totally absorbed in her book.

tr: giving or marked by complete attention to
example: that engrossed look or rapt delight
so intent on this fantastic...narrative that she hardly stirred"- Walter de la Mar

value.def: If you are absorbed in something or someone, you are very interested in them and they take up all your attention and energy.

example.ex: They were completely absorbed in each other...
He had discovered politics and was rapidly becoming absorbed by it...
example.tran: 他接触到了政治并且迅速地对它着了迷。

example.ex: I get so absorbed in doing something that I am unaware of things happening round me.
example.tran: 我做事太过专心以致于对周围发生的事情丝毫未察觉。

value.tran: 极感兴趣的；专心的；全神贯注的

trans: 结合水；吸附水；吸着水；吸著水；吸收水
